ENTRY       EC 4.2.1.105                Enzyme
NAME        2-hydroxyisoflavanone dehydratase;
            2,7,4'-trihydroxyisoflavanone hydro-lyase;
            2,7,4'-trihydroxyisoflavanone hydro-lyase (daidzein-forming)
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-oxygen lyases;
            Hydro-lyases
SYSNAME     2,4',7-trihydroxyisoflavanone hydro-lyase (daidzein-forming)
REACTION    (1) 2,4',7-trihydroxyisoflavanone = daidzein + H2O [RN:R07317];
            (2) 2,4',5,7-tetrahydroxyisoflavanone = genistein + H2O
ALL_REAC    R07317;
            (other) R06793 R07723
SUBSTRATE   2,4',7-trihydroxyisoflavanone;
            2,4',5,7-tetrahydroxyisoflavanone
PRODUCT     daidzein [CPD:C10208];
            H2O [CPD:C00001];
            genistein [CPD:C06563]
COMMENT     Catalyses the final step in the formation of the isoflavonoid skeleton. The reaction also occurs spontaneously.
HISTORY     EC 4.2.1.105 created 2004, modified 2013
REFERENCE   1
  AUTHORS   Hakamatsuka, T., Mori, K., Ishida, S., Ebizuka, Y and Sankawa, U.
  TITLE     Purification of 2-hydroxyisoflavanone dehydratase from the cell cultures of Pueraria lobata.
  JOURNAL   Phytochemistry 49 (1998) 497-505.
PATHWAY     ec00943  Isoflavonoid biosynthesis
            ec01110  Biosynthesis of secondary metabolites
